}}{{TIDTOC|embedded}} ==Overview== Same hardware as the [[D-Link DIR-636L rev A1]]. Assumed [[Cameo]] device. :This device is using [http://www.MediaTek.com/en/News/news_content.php?sn=1057 RT6856]. The Ralink chip used for the on-board wireless again appears to be RT5592 (RTL5592EPL?).
{{WiFiCert|WFA14995|04/03/2012}}
The default SSID formats for the device are '''dlink-XXXX''' (2.4 GHz) and '''dlink-media-XXXX''' (5 GHz), where '''XXXX''' appears to be the last two bytes (upper case letters) of the respective interface's MAC address.
